  "name": "Pneumonia - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds + Procedures)",
  "description": "Simulates a hospitalist identifying their complete pneumonia patient population. Combines: pneumonia diagnosis codes (multi-etiology), antibiotics, and chest X-ray procedures. Tests Condition + MedicationRequest + Procedure resource union for acute infection.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete pneumonia patient population for a quality improvement initiative on antibiotic stewardship and timely imaging. From clinical experience, pneumonia patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal pneumonia diagnosis (community-acquired, nosocomial, bacterial, or viral), most are on antibiotics (azithromycin, ceftriaxone, amoxicillin, levofloxacin, doxycycline), and most have undergone chest X-ray for confirmation.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any pneumonia diagnosis\n2. Patients prescribed pneumonia antibiotics\n3. Patients who have undergone chest X-ray\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found. Note: antibiotics have heavy cross-indication with other infections, so the diagnosis and procedure paths are more specific.",
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "multi_query": true,
    "algorithm_path": "comprehensive",
    "algorithm_path_description": "Union of pneumonia dx + antibiotic Rx + chest X-ray Procedure. Tests Condition + MedicationRequest + Procedure cross-resource union for acute infection.",
